<p>The <code>tag</code> function wraps a value as a PAD tag (alias for <code>open</code>).</p>

<h2>Basic Usage</h2>
<pre>{open}'myTag' | tag{close}</pre>
<p>Result: <b>{'myTag' | tag}</b></p>

<h2>Dynamic Tag Names</h2>
<pre>{open}$tagName = 'users'{close}
{open}$tagName | tag{close}</pre>
{data $tagName = 'users'}
<p>Dynamic tag: <b>{$tagName | tag}</b></p>

<h2>Chained Examples</h2>
<pre>{open}'IF' | lower | tag{close}</pre>
<p>Lowercase tag: <b>{'IF' | lower | tag}</b></p>

<pre>{open}'my_tag' | replace('_', '') | tag{close}</pre>
<p>Clean tag name: <b>{'my_tag' | replace('_', '') | tag}</b></p>

<h2>Note</h2>
<p>The <code>tag</code> function is useful for dynamically generating PAD tag syntax. It's equivalent to wrapping a value in braces.</p>
